<style>
body
{
    color: #363942;
    background-image: url(../images/ricepaper.png);
}

h1
{
    text-align: center;
    font-variant: small-caps;
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 3.5em;
}

h3
{
    text-align: center;
    font-variant: small-caps;
    line-height: .5em;
}

#menu
{
    /*Make a box with rounded corners.*/
    border-radius: 15px; /*Give the box a light shadow.*/
    box-shadow: 0px 0px 1px #000000; /*The width of the box must be a bit larger than the width of the paragraph.*/
    position: fixed;
}

#menu ul
{
    margin: 0.5em;
    padding: 0.5em;
    list-style-type: none;
    font-size: x-large;
}

#menu ul li
{
    padding-top: 1em;
    padding-bottom: 1em;
}

#menu ul li a
{
    text-decoration: none;
    color: #5C832F;
}

#menu ul li a:hover
{
    color: #284907;
}

#intro
{
    padding-bottom: 1em;
}

#intro p
{
    font-size: large;
    width: 20em;
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: auto;
    text-align: justify;
}

blockquote
{
    background-color: #FFF7FE;
}

blockquote p
{
    width: 21em;
    text-indent: 0em;
    margin-top: 1em;
    margin-bottom: 1em;
}

/*
    The "main" div and the <p> selectors took a lot of fiddling and are where most of the action occurs.  Ease of readability is paramount.
*/

#main
{
    /*Make a box with rounded corners.*/
    border-radius: 15px; /*Give the box a light shadow.*/
    box-shadow: 0px 0px 10px #000000; /*The width of the box must be a bit larger than the width of the paragraph.*/
    width: 48.5em; /*The width setting, along with these margin settings, put the box in the center with the sides hugging the text.*/
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: auto;
    padding-top: 1em;
    padding-bottom: 1em; /*Contrast is greater than outside the essay in order to focus the readers' attention.*/
    background-color: #F0F8FF;
    color: #382513;
}

#main hr
{
    width: 25%;
}

p
{
    /*Short lines mean that the eyes don't travel far in order to read.*/
    width: 28em; /*There's very little padding so that the box hugs the paragraphs.  The lines of the box guide the eyes downward.*/
    padding-top: 0.12em;
    padding-bottom: 0.12em; /*Jagged right edges are unsightly, so I justify paragraphs.  Lines are short, so readability is unaffected.*/
    text-align: justify; /*I try to imitate printed copy with the justified and indented paragraphs.*/
    text-indent: 4em;
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: auto;
    margin-bottom: 0;
    margin-top: 0; /*Between the short lines and the large letters, I'm trying to entice readers to go on.  "Just another line.  It's not much."*/
    font-size: x-large;
}

/*
    The extro tells how the essay was received, who linked to it, and any discussion on it.  I write the extro some time after publishing the essay.
*/

#extro
{
    padding-top: 1em;
    padding-bottom: 1em;
}

#extro p
{
    font-size: large;
    width: 20em;
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: auto;
    text-align: justify;
}

#footer p
{
    padding: none;
    font-size: smaller;
    text-align: center;
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: auto;
    width: 30em;
}
</style>
